A vintage 1960s spy thriller style illustration showing a rotary telephone receiver connected by a curling cord that transforms into a dotted line snaking across a stylized world map, with small radar-like concentric circles pulsing from a mysterious location. The color palette features muted teals, burnt oranges, and cream tones with subtle paper texture and halftone printing effects. A silhouetted figure in a trench coat stands in the corner, peering at the map through binoculars. The composition evokes Cold War era surveillance paranoia with a touch of retro playfulness.
